description:
"Pleasure Synthesis: The story of SUPERHYPERCUBE" by Heather Kelley at the 2016 Gray Area Festival.

This talk covers the inspirations and design concepts behind kokoromi's upcoming PlaystationVR launch title SUPERHYPERCUBE. Starting from the game's origins in 2008 as a stereoscopic game using DIY headtracking and red/cyan 3D glasses, and reaching to the present in full color and sound, kokoromi member Heather Kelley will explore how a decade of experimentation has shaped kokoromi's game design process, and how this abstract game invokes the immersive sensory pleasure that VR has always promised, along with its complicated relationship to embodied "reality."

The Gray Area Festival is four days of conference, performances, workshops, and exhibitions to discuss the impact of art and technology on culture. More at http://grayareafestival.io
